{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489638"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:24:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:24:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"706"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"706","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/706"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.34,0.1,0.39,0.05,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"706"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107318"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"706","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/706"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"706"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89781"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"434"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7869"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7908"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19237"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43971"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107318"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman presents with a five month history of gradual deterioration in her vision. Her current health issues include hypertension, type 2 diabetes and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. She smokes 20 cigarettes a day and has two standard drinks a day. She is on perindopril and gliclazide. Her visual acuity is 6/24 in each eye. With the use of a pinhole the vision improves to 6/9 in the right eye and 6/6 in the left eye.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely explanation for the visual loss?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Age-related macular degeneration","Chronic open angle glaucoma","Cataracts","Hypertensive retinopathy","Diabetic retinopathy"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient is an older woman who has presented with gradual deterioration of her vision which has improved with using a pinhole. A pinhole test is a simple method that is used for distinguishing decreased visual acuity due to a refractive error from other reasons like degenerative changes and pathological conditions. A pinhole test eliminates all the surrounding refracting light rays and allows only a very small, straight and parallel light rays to pass from outside the retina directly on to the macula. Of the options, only \u003Cstrong\u003Ecataracts\u003C/strong\u003E can cause a refractive error.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAge-related macular degeneration\u003C/strong\u003E (ARMD) is a common, chronic, progressive degenerative disorder of the macula that affects older individuals and features loss of central vision as a result of abnormalities in the photoreceptor/retinal pigment epithelium/Bruch\u2019s membrane/choroidal complex often resulting in geographic atrophy and/or neovascularisation. Smoking and alcohol can be risk factors for ARMD, but vision loss in ARMD does not improve with a pinhole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic open angle glaucoma\u003C/strong\u003E is due to aqueous drainage problems causing raised intraocular pressure and gradual asymptomatic peripheral field loss and only central visual loss at the end stage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypertensive retinopathy\u003C/strong\u003E can be present in smokers and hypertensive patients, it is characterised by characteristic retinal changes but it is not associated with improvement with a pinhole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetic retinopathy \u003C/strong\u003Eis present in patients with uncontrolled diabetes and is characterised by retinal changes that lead to decreased visual acuity. The visual acuity in diabetic retinopathy does not improve with a pinhole because of its presence in the retina, not the refracting pathway.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cataracts are characterised by observing improved visual acuity with a pinhole."],"references":["Green C, Goodfellow J, Kubie J. Eye care in the elderly. Aust Fam Physician 2014;43(7):444-7 Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/afp/2014/july/eye-care-in-the-elderly","American Academy of Ophthalmology. Cataract \u2013 EyeWiki. EyeWiki 2024 Available at: https://eyewiki.org/Cataract","Fong A, Lee G. Reducing vision loss in chronic eye disease. Aust Fam Physician 2009;38(10):774-9 Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/afp/2009/october/reducing-vision-loss","Cataracts: From One Medical Student to Another. EyeRounds.org - Ophthalmology - The University of Iowa [Internet]. Eyerounds.org. 2019 [cited 2024 Nov 12]. Available at: https://eyerounds.org/tutorials/cataract-for-Med-Students/index.htm#gsc.tab=0"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89781"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"706"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89781","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89781"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-27T21:57:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-27T21:57:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"706"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107318"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","na